\

\b\fs28 Mac OS 10.7 (Lion)
\b0\fs24 \
\
This distribution works on Lion.\
\

\b\fs28 Mac OS 10.8 (Mountain Lion)
\b0\fs24 \
\
This distribution works on Mountain Lion, but Mountain Lion does not come with X11 installed, so you must download and install {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://xquartz.macosforge.org/"}}{\fldrslt XQuartz}}. Mountain Lion also has a default setting where only applications signed by Apple and developers will run. This is a good setting for security, so rather than change it, we recommend that you right click the otterlace app and choose "Open" to run it the first time. You'll then be presented with a dialog to confirm that you want to make a permanent exception to allow otterlace to run.\

\b\fs28 \
Mac OS software updates
\b0\fs24 \
\
If you have installed XQuartz, as recommended above, you will need to re-install it after running any Mac OS software updates, so keep a copy of the DMG file ready.\
\

